We hope that our Facebook group has been enjoyable, educational, and life-changing in some way, whether it be a shift in your perspective towards smoking, or a commitment towards a healthier, smoke-free life. All of us at TSP have enjoyed reading your comments and interacting with you online, and we truly thank you for your participation. Although we will no longer be posting daily, you are welcome to remain in this secret group and access all of the content we've shared over the past 90 days. Furthermore, we're still available to answer any questions/concerns about smoking, and we're open to any feedback/suggestions you may have for our program. Again, from all of us at TSP, thank you and good luck in your future endeavors!

Yeah, those are all very common triggers. What could you alternatively do after eating, drinking, or to de-stress?

I agree, especially when you try to quit smoking it may initially be a good idea to reduce your alcohol use as well, as this tends to lead to high risk situations for relapse. After eating you may want to consider just brushing your teeth, using some sugar free gum or hard candy, or simply a toothpick in your mouth to distract yourself from smoking. Have you thought more about nicotine replacement at all?

I am just asking because I think nicotine replacement may be able to help you reduce your overall level of craving. Do you think you will give it a try?

Yes, I would definitely encourage you to try some form of nicotine replacement once you are ready to quit. What would you need to feel more successful?
I've got to run. See you next week!

FACT: Research shows that although some people quit cold turkey successfully, the most effective way to quit smoking is using a combo of counseling plus nicotine replacement therapy (NRT, like patch or gum) or medicine (like bupropion SR). What have you heard about NRT’s? Would you consider using NRT? #beingconscious
It's a possibility

I've smoke vase before but I'd rather smoke cigarettes

My grandma and my mom

data.message: Most people who smoke report their top reason for smoking is to deal with stress: work, class, family, friends, significant others- it can be a lot! So can you think of another way you could deal with stress that won’t force you into lighting up when things get tough? What could you do instead? #balance
Besides doing stress relieving exercises and hobbies I'm not sure
How could you have a more active lifestyle without smoking? #balance
Playing disc golf
Post your wish list here! #balance
A new car or laptop
Hi guys, how were everyone's holidays? Did you have to face any specific cravings or smoking triggers?
Daily stress
Hi 10010 - yes daily stress is a big one, and you are certainly not the only one facing this issue. Are there any other ways to reduce your stress other than smoking you can think of?
Finding a hobby but Idk what I could do

10010 exercise is a great way to reduce your stress. I can also recommend a couple of simple techniques for relieving stress, like visualization and imagery or deep relaxation. Have you ever tried stress reduction techniques?
Family.
Yes 10014, others can really trigger our smoking, right? But some people can also help us to reduce or quit. Do you have anyone in your life that can support and motivate you?
No actually I haven't

10010, one option is imagery - Imagery means picturing or imagining something in your mind. Find somewhere quiet where you can be alone. Visualize a scene that makes you feel more relaxed. Then, focus on your senses (what do you see? Hear? Smell? Taste? Feel against your skin?)
some other ideas just for fun:
True.

The other method is deep breathing relaxation. This is one of the simplest relaxation methods, based upon a meditative, deep-breathing technique. And just like any other skill; practice makes perfect!
Too bad I couldn't actually be at the beach
haha, I hear ya 10010 :) Do you think any of these could work for you? Feel free to give them a try - in my experience they can really help with reducing stress!
I'll try it
Honestly what i do is just avoid my family & spend the holidays with my friends
Lol I escape the holidays with my family and end up spending it with the boyfriend's family for thanksgiving for example
10014 & 10010: How could others like your friends help you or encourage you to quit? Any thoughts what they could do to help?
I've got to run, guys. Feel free to try the stress reduction techniques or to comment on the social support issue during the week if you'd like. We can continue to talk next week. See ya!
Unfortunately all my friends smoke

Yesterday we asked you to tell us how confident you were that you COULD quit smoking if you wanted to. What would it take to get you from the number you said yesterday to ONE NUMBER HIGHER? #motivation
I honestly wish I could get rid of the things in my life stressing me out then I probably could stop
We understand that stopping smoking is not easy. On a scale of 1-10, how confident are you that you COULD quit smoking if you tried? #motivation
Probably a 4. Have a lot going on right now that I probably couldnt

data.message: What is keeping quitting smoking from the top of your priorities list? What would make quitting even more important to you? #motivation
If I started having health issues
Do you think you will ever want to quit smoking? When? #motivation
One day just not sure when.
Sure just not now
On a scale of 1-10, how important is it to you to quit smoking for good? #motivation
Right now it's at a 3
1 or 2
How would you react if you found out your son or daughter smoked cigarettes?  #motivation
i would tell them the risk factors that could happen if they start smoking. Ask them why they decided to start
What’s the worst thing that could happen if you don’t quit smoking? #motivation
Cancer,  copd
Hi everyone and welcome to TSP! I am available for the next hour. Let me know if you have any questions!

I gotta run guys. You were pretty quiet today so I am going to leave you with a fun quiz that you can try over the holidays. Are you curious to find out more about your smoking?   Trythis SHORT survey about why you smoke (Don’t worry it’s easy)STOP when you get your score. https://ucsf.co1.qualtrics.com/SE/?SID=SV_73dz87ACkEB28vPWhich categories did you score 11 or higher? If you didn’t score 11 or higher in any of them, which were your 2 highest scores?

A high score in Stimulation suggests thatyou are a smoker who is stimulated by the cigarette — you feel that it helps wake you, organize your thoughts, and keep you going.A high score in Handling suggests that youfeel satisfied by handling cigarettes.A high score in Pleasure Relaxationsuggests that using cigarettes makes you feel good.A high score in Crutch: Tension Reductionsuggests you use cigarettes as a crutch in moments of stress or discomfort.A high score in Craving: PsychologicalAddiction suggests you are psychologically addicted to cigarettes. Quittingsmoking is difficult for the person who is psychologically addicted.A high score in Habit suggests that you nolonger getting much satisfaction from cigarettes.
Does that fit with why you think you smoke?Reminding yourself of these reasons will help you to get a better understanding of your smoking behavior.
What would be the best-case scenario if you quit smoking? #motivation
I would help my mom to quit smoking best case scenario we both would start living healthier lives
What was your reason for picking up that first cigarette? Was it to be cool and independent, to experiment, to look older, something else? #beingconscious

I worked at a liquor store and at the holidays employees are not allowed to go out side on breaks unless you smoke. We would be inside that store working 10 his a day and  I didn't want to be inside so I picked up smoking. It was a bad idea
How would you support someone who tells you they want to quit smoking? #motivation

if someone asked me to help them quit smoking, i would quit to and tell them that any time that they feel the need to smoke they could come talk to me and we would get through it together. We would find something that would keep our minds off wanting to smoke.
Thanks for sharing, 10010! -Ali from TSP
Share a success that you have had in the past. It can be anything from any time. Why did it work? Who helped? #motivation
Does it have to involve smoking?
My mom convinced me to quit for a couple weeks
It worked because she smokes and I learned a lot
Hi 10010. It can be any success, not just smoking!
I used to work for a chiropractic office and working hard during training and doing the best I could helped me become very successful with the patients and all of the paperwork
What are some of your favorite qualities about yourself?  How does smoking fit (or not fit) with that image of you? #balance

data.message: Welcome to the Tobacco Status Project! Thank you for joining us -- we're so excited to have you here. We're going to start posting TODAY (in about an hour)! Here's how it works:1) We will share one post everyday for 90 days. Remember to check this page daily!2) To earn money, you must comment on a post on the day that it was posted. You will receive $1 every day that you comment. This will come in a gift card at the end of the 90-day program3) Dr. Johannes Thrull will be joining us for 1 hour each week, during which he will answer any tobacco-related questions, share info and resources, and provide support to our group. Stay tuned for his first session next week!Look for today's post soon! - Ali from TSP
